nly path collects all list values into a `Vec<String>` and immediately iterates over them to parse hashes. Parsing each row as it comes back from rusqlite would avoid an extra allocation proportional to the stored transcript list.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=333 end=337 priority=3 confidence=0.8}\\n\\nI did not edit files. Sanity check: `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets -- -D warnings` passes.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:48:12.238Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}